<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 28 at 10:41AM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Areas of Snow With Slippery Spots through Mid Day...
Through 1230 PM, areas of primarily light snow over southeastern
Lee, much of LaSalle, southern DeKalb, and northwestern Grundy
Counties will gradually wind down. A smaller pocket of heavier
snow over northwestern Kendall County should gradually taper in
intensity, though lake effect snow may push into far northeast
Kendall County. Expect variable conditions, with roads reported
to be partly to mostly snow covered in spots. If you will be
driving, leave extra time to reach your destination. When driving
on snow covered roads, slow down and increase following distance
between your vehicle and other vehicles.</description>
